        <h1>
         ISCOR: an innovative, multi-disciplinary program that allows
              you to achieve your full potential.
        </h1>
        <table border="0" cellpadding="8" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
         <tr align="left" valign="top">
          <td width="60%">
           <p>
            The International Security and Conflict Resolution (ISCOR) major at San Diego State University is an innovative, interdisciplinary program designed to provide students with a sophisticated understanding of the political, moral, socio-economic, and cultural dimensions to global conflict. Its interest extends well beyond conventional international security issues to encompass the broader analysis of global affairs, with an in-depth focus on global justice and the environment. Thus, ISCOR exposes students to a multiplicity of ideological, regional, and cultural perspectives with the aim of making ISCOR students informed global citizens able to critically examine claims made by public officials and other partisans and discover underlying realities. In the course of their studies, students will attain a comprehensive and multifaceted understanding of global affairs and appreciate the many challenges to building a more peaceful, just and ecologically sustainable global order. Similarly, ISCOR students will develop a rich appreciation of both increased global interconnections (sometimes known as globalization) and enduring diversity in cultural practices, political systems, and economic systems.
           </p>
           <p>
            <a href="program_info.htm">
             Read more about the ISCOR program.
            </a>
           </p>
           <h3>
            <br/>
            <br/>
            In Memoriam: Dr. David H. Johns
           </h3>
           <p>
            We are deeply saddened to announce that Dr. John's died suddenly on Feburary 27, 2017. He had a long career in the Political Science Department and was a co-founder of the ISCOR Program. A Celebration of Life ceremony will be held on Saturday, April 15 at 2:00 PM at United Church of Christ (5940 Kelton Ave., La Mesa, CA).
            <a href="http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/sandiegouniontribune/obituary.aspx?n=david-hoogland-johns&amp;pid=184413669">
             More information.
            </a>
           </p>
           <p>
            <br/>
            In lieu of flowers, his family asks that you make a contribution to the ISCOR scholarship fund.   You can contribute:
           </p>
           <ol>
            <li>
             <a href="https://securelb.imodules.com/s/997/campaign13/index.aspx?sid=997&amp;gid=1&amp;pgid=3034&amp;dids=440&amp;bledit=1">
              Online through a secure system
             </a>
             .
             <br/>
             <br/>
             or
             <br/>
             <br/>
            </li>
            <li>
             By check. Please make checks payable to “SDSU Campanile Foundation” and put “ISCOR scholarship” in the memo line.
             <br/>
             <br/>
             Send checks to:
             <br/>
             <br/>
             San Diego State University
             <br/>
             Political Science Department
             <br/>
             5500 Campanile Dr., NH 126
             <br/>
             San Diego, CA 92182-4427
            </li>
           </ol>
           <p>
           </p>
